George Mitchell has resigned as the U.S. Special Envoy for the Middle East after serving for two and a half years. He has been commended for his commitment to peace and democracy in the region. Mitchell's resignation letter states that he initially intended to serve for two years and expresses support for the President's vision of comprehensive peace in the Middle East. Secretary Clinton also praises Mitchell's dedication and leadership, and expresses confidence in the Deputy Middle East Envoy, David Hale, to continue making progress in the peace efforts.